SUMMARY:Creative Writing Series: Summer Farah\, Poetry
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260416T233000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260417T003000Z
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51534123490206
DESCRIPTION:Please join us for the next event in the 2025-2026 Creative Wr
 iting Series: a poetry reading and Q&A featuring poet\, essayist and zine-
 maker Summer Farah!\n\nThis event is free and open to all\, and will be av
 ailable in person and livestreamed.\n \n\nSummer Farah is a Palestinian Am
 erican writer\, editor\, and zine-maker from California. She is the author
  of The Hungering Years (Host Publications\, 2026) and the chapbook I coul
 d die today and live again (Game Over Books\, 2024). Her essay "From Witne
 ss From Speech From Image: On Etel Adnan’s The Arab Apocalypse and There
 sa Hak Kyung Cha’s Dictee" received a 2025 Krause Essay Prize honorable 
 mention. Summer is a member of the Radius of Arab American Writers and the
  National Book Critics Circle. She is calling on you to recommit yourself 
 to the liberation of the Palestinian people each day.\n \n\nThis event is 
 co-sponsored with the Department of Middle East/South Asia Studies.\n \n\n
 The Creative Writing Series is presented by the UC Davis Department of Eng
 lish\, Creative Writing Master of Fine Arts Program\,\nand the UC Davis Li
 brary.\n\nThe views expressed in this series\, including descriptions and 
 biographies\, are those of the speakers and not meant to represent the vie
 ws of any other person or institution.
LOCATION:Shields Library\, 205
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/creative-writing-series-summe
 r-farah-poetry
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Silent Reading Hour at Shields
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260417T000000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260417T010000Z
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52208562394281
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a silent reading hour at Shields Library! We'll ha
 ve snacks on hand and a quiet space to read just for fun.\n\nDrop in any t
 ime between 5-6 p.m. witih a book — physical\, digital\, audio + headpho
 nes (we don't judge!). Or pick something from our reading cart. \n\nStick 
 around after for a cover selfie and meet fellow readers.
LOCATION:Shields Library\, 205 Library Instruction Room
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/silent-reading-meet-up
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Collaborative Data Science Office Hours (virtual)
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260420T200000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260420T210000Z
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_50756015395972
DESCRIPTION:DataLab and colleagues from research computing and statistical
  service units across UC Davis offer weekly free virtual office hours duri
 ng which UC Davis researchers can obtain help and advice on working with t
 heir data. During these short\, just-in-time sessions we meet with faculty
 \, students\, postdoctoral scholars\, and research staff from all domains 
 across the University to discuss their research challenges.\n\nRegister in
  advance for the Zoom link. This helps us connect you to the right expert 
 for your question.\n\nIn addition to DataLab\, the collaborative data scie
 nce office hours are supported by:\n\nBiostatistics (Clinical and Translat
 ional Science Center\, CTSC)Computational Research Data Service (College o
 f Letters & Science)High Performance Computing (HPC) CoreResearcher Servic
 es (UC Davis Library)Stat Lab (Department of Statistics)Common office hour
 s help topics include:\n\nOpen Source Programming (R\, Python\, Julia\, et
 c.)Reproducible research computing and data scienceResponsible and ethical
  data scienceData gathering\, organization\, databases\, and experimental 
 designData analysis\, statistics\, and explorationData visualizationMachin
 e learning and neural networksText mining and natural language processingG
 eospatial sciencesRemote and high performance computingComputational pedag
 ogy… and more!Please note that drop-in office hours are not offered duri
 ng University holidays\, academic breaks and finals week. Summer schedule 
 varies based on availability.\n\nNote: Office hours are intended for short
  "just in time" research support. If you require extensive assistance we m
 ay refer you a recharge service\, upcoming funding/project calls\, and/or 
 other resources. We are unable to provide support for assigned coursework 
 (homework assignments\, class projects\, etc.) during office hours. If you
  need such help please contact your instructor or TA for assistance. If yo
 u need help with technical problems such system administration and hardwar
 e issues\, check out the the UC Davis ServiceHub and/or contact your depar
 tmental IT.
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/copy-of-collaborative-data-sc
 ience-office-hours-virtual
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Davis R Users' Group
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260421T170000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260421T190000Z
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51754758586316
DESCRIPTION:D-RUG\, our local R Users' Group\, meets weekly to facilitate 
 learning and using the R software language. R users from all domains are i
 nvited to bring their R-specific coding problems and share their experienc
 e with other members of the community. Meetup formats include everything f
 rom group discussion and mini-workshops to coworking sessions. D-RUG is ru
 n by volunteer Coo[R]dinators including UC Davis data scientists and gradu
 ate students dedicated to growing and strengthening the R community.\n\n \
 n\nToday's session is open-forum format to foster a communal\, co-working 
 environment. Come hang out and chat\, work on your own\, seek and give hel
 p\, and make friends.\n\n \n\nD-RUG meets Thursdays in person from 10 AM t
 o 12 PM at the DataLab Classroom (Shields Library room 360) on the UC Davi
 s campus. \n\nSign up for our mailing list to get the most up to date info
 rmation\, including a Zoom link to join us virtually if you can't make it 
 in person. Learn more about D-RUG on our website.
LOCATION:Shields Library\, 360
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/davis-r-users-group-2026
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:DataLab Office Hours (in person)
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260421T200000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260421T210000Z
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_50755967519434
DESCRIPTION:DataLab offers free in person drop-in office hours during whic
 h UC Davis researchers can obtain data science help and advice on working 
 with their data. During these short\, just-in-time sessions we meet with f
 aculty\, students\, postdoctoral scholars\, and staff from all domains acr
 oss the University. Depending on the nature of your question and our avail
 ability\, it may be possible to schedule a longer follow-up consultation a
 fter your office hours visit.\n\nAppointments are not required. Please com
 plete the brief office hours intake form ahead of time to help us connect 
 you with the right expert for your question.\n\nCommon office hours help t
 opics include:\n\nOpen Source Programming (R\, Python\, Julia\, etc.)Repro
 ducible research computing and data scienceResponsible and ethical data sc
 ienceData gathering\, organization\, databases\, and experimental designDa
 ta analysis\, statistics\, and explorationData visualizationMachine learni
 ng and neural networksText mining and natural language processingGeospatia
 l sciencesRemote and high performance computingComputational pedagogy… a
 nd more!Please note that drop-in office hours are not offered during Unive
 rsity holidays\, academic breaks and finals week. Summer schedule varies. 
 DataLab may only be accessed during Shields Library's business hours. Clic
 k here for detailed directions to DataLab.\n\nNote: We are unable to provi
 de support for assigned coursework (homework assignments\, class projects\
 , etc.) during office hours. If you need such help please contact your ins
 tructor or TA for assistance. If you need help with technical problems suc
 h system administration and hardware issues\, check out the the UC Davis S
 erviceHub and/or contact your departmental IT.
LOCATION:Shields Library\, 360
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/copy-of-datalab-office-hours-
 in-person
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Emerging Topics: Pop-Up Talk
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260424T200000Z
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260424T210000Z
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51843766520718
DESCRIPTION:DataLab's pop-up talks are by DataLab faculty\, staff\, and af
 filiates and focus on emerging topics\, tips\, and trends in data science.
  Join us for the Winter 2026 series on alternating Fridays from 1-2 PM at 
 DataLab. After the talk stick around for refreshments during our weekly so
 cial "Data Science Cafe" from 2-3 PM.\n\n \n\nThis event is offered in per
 son. All members of the University of California system are welcome to att
 end. Advance registration requested but not required!\n\n \n\nCan’t atte
 nd this event? Materials from prior UC Davis DataLab workshops are availab
 le on DataLab's website. Check out our workshop schedule for other upcomin
 g trainings. Questions? Email datalab-training@ucdavis.edu. \n\n \n\nQuest
 ions? Contact datalab-training@ucdavis.edu.
LOCATION:Shields Library\, 360
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/pop-up-talk-w2026-0426
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
